      { text: "Hepatocytes causing granulomatous hepatitis", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "M. leprae has essentially no hepatic tropism given its strict preference for cool peripheral tissues; hepatic granulomas are characteristic of TB and sarcoidosis; leprosy virtually never causes clinically significant liver disease." }
