      { text: "Post-traumatic epilepsy (antibiotics reduce seizure risk)", type: "misconception", distanceScore: 2, distanceLabel: "Common misconception", explanation: "Antibiotics have no effect on post-traumatic seizure risk; seizure prophylaxis is addressed through anti-epileptic medication (levetiracetam or phenytoin); conflating CNS infection prophylaxis with seizure prevention reflects a misunderstanding of the distinct pathophysiological mechanisms involved." },
      { text: "Hospital-acquired pneumonia from prolonged ICU stay", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "VAP prophylaxis involves ventilator bundles, oral decontamination, and head positioning; antibiotics for penetrating brain injury specifically target CNS infection and surgical site infection, not anticipated respiratory complications; the indication and target organisms are completely different." }
