      { text: "Inhibits NFkB preventing pyrin inflammasome gene transcription", type: "misconception", distanceScore: 2, distanceLabel: "Common misconception", explanation: "NFkB inhibition and transcriptional suppression characterize corticosteroids; colchicine acts post-translationally by disrupting tubulin polymerization, not by inhibiting gene transcription; this mechanistic distinction explains why colchicine effects are immediate and do not require protein turnover as corticosteroids do." },
      { text: "Anti-tumor necrosis factor activity reducing systemic inflammation", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "Anti-TNF agents (infliximab, etanercept, adalimumab) block TNF-alpha signaling; colchicine has no anti-TNF activity; TNF inhibitors have actually been associated with paradoxical worsening of FMF attacks in case reports; colchicine efficacy is entirely through microtubule disruption and inflammasome impairment." }
