      { text: "Red-brown lines on the sclera", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "Scleral changes are not a recognized manifestation of lead poisoning; Kayser-Fleischer rings (green-brown copper deposits at the corneal periphery) occur in Wilson disease; Burton lines are specifically located at the dental gum margin as blue-black deposits; scleral involvement from lead toxicity is not a described clinical finding." }
