      { text: "HIV accelerates lymphocutaneous spread but does not cause dissemination", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "HIV does cause dissemination beyond lymphocutaneous spread. In patients with CD4 <100-200, Sporothrix hematogenously disseminates to joints, bones, CNS, and multiple skin sites throughout the body. This is true disseminated infection, not merely accelerated local lymphangitic spread." }
