      { text: "Levofloxacin 500mg for 7 days covers both pathogens", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "Levofloxacin has no role in gonorrhea treatment due to ubiquitous fluoroquinolone resistance in N. gonorrhoeae globally. While levofloxacin covers Chlamydia trachomatis (used in PID treatment regimens when gonorrhea has been excluded), it cannot replace ceftriaxone for gonococcal coverage." }
