      { text: "Throat gargling with antiseptic solution plus oral antibiotics", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "Antiseptic gargling has no role in gonorrhea treatment and would not achieve bactericidal concentrations in the pharyngeal mucosa where N. gonorrhoeae resides. Systemic antibiotic therapy (IM ceftriaxone) is required to achieve adequate mucosal drug levels for pharyngeal gonorrhea eradication." }
