      { text: "Routine HCV vaccination for healthcare workers", type: "misconception", distanceScore: 2, distanceLabel: "Common misconception", explanation: "No HCV vaccine exists despite decades of research; the error likely confuses HCV with HBV, for which an effective vaccine is part of standard healthcare worker immunization programs; the absence of an HCV vaccine makes prevention strategies entirely behavioral." },
      { text: "Isolation of HCV-positive patients from other patients", type: "wildly_wrong", distanceScore: 3, distanceLabel: "Way off", explanation: "HCV is not transmitted by casual contact, respiratory droplets, or environmental surfaces; isolation of HCV-positive patients is not indicated under any guideline and would constitute stigmatizing discrimination; standard blood and body fluid precautions are sufficient." }
